<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Attendant" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Attendant,</orth> servant: <cit><quote>here have I few --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 166</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.150.128" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 2, 5</bibl> <cit><quote>(the ladies, her --s of her chamber).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 40.</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.258" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 258</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 2, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.132" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 132</bibl>. Followed by <emph>on</emph>: <cit><quote>lately a. on the Duke of Norfolk,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 101</bibl></cit>. -- In <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 21</bibl>; <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 8</bibl>; <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 132</bibl>, it may be also == companion.
